  "prompt": "You convert natural language software requirements into UML state machine diagrams in PlantUML format.\n\nRules:\n\n- Output ONLY PlantUML code.\n\n- Start with @startuml and end with @enduml.\n\n- Use [*] for exactly one initial transition.\n\n- Use --> for transitions.\n\n- Include transition labels when requirement evidence exists.\n\n- Do not add explanations or markdown fences.\n\nTarget requirement:\n\nInventory — Polished Requirement Specification\n\nFunctional Requirements\n1. The system shall allow the user to add new goods to the inventory.\n2. The system shall allow the user to update the price of existing items in the inventory.\n3. The system shall allow the user to remove goods from the inventory that are no longer required.\n4. The system shall identify expired goods and notify the user about their removal from the inventory.\n5. The system shall allow the user to place an order to a supplier for additional goods when required.\n6. The system shall generate an invoice for the order once it is placed.\n7. The system shall allow the user to search for items available in the inventory and select them for purchase.\n8. The system shall calculate the applicable discount and tax based on the selected items.\n9. The system shall generate a receipt for the customer after the purchase.\n10. The system shall allow the user to replace an item or cancel the receipt during the billing process if needed.\n11. The system shall record customer requests for items that may not be currently available.\n12. The system shall allow the user to view a summary report of all transactions carried out in the system at any point.\n\nNow return only the final PlantUML.\n",
